            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "Worst infrastructure ever. Had gone for a interschool competition. They didn't have any arrangements to cater to kids. In harsh summer like this, they only had a tent as a provision.\nNo understanding of how an event should be organised, 5 yr olds who were to start the competition at 10, were waiting till 2.\nVery sad state of affairs by the school management.\nParents should stay away from such institutions.\nTo top it off, when we raised this issue to the principal, she said if you have a problem you can walk out of the competition.",
